  "summary": "Keyword co-occurrence in bundled output without traced exfiltration path",
  "details": "Pattern matches fired on co-occurrence of the tokens 'ping', 'POST', and 'hostname' across a bundled JavaScript file (dist/chunk-ALPYR2GC.js, dist/chunk-R7QYGZUP.cjs) and the corresponding source (src/init.ts). The matched tokens are spread across hundreds of lines (e.g., 'POST' at line ~105, 'ping' at line ~1060, 'hostname' at line ~640) rather than co-located in a single exfiltration call site, which is the typical shape of a benign bundle that happens to mention each keyword in unrelated functions. No hardcoded attacker-controlled endpoint, credential-path read, env-var scrape, lifecycle-hook execution, or browser/wallet enumeration was identified. Without a traced data-flow tying installer-side data to a network sink, the signal does not meet the bar for a supply-chain block. Routing to human review for confirmation.",
